            <div>
               
	<pb facs="liv_001193_0001" n="0001"/><!-- Change both @facs and @n -->
	<!-- Start each page with a <pb> formatted as above -->

<!-- If this is a letter or similar with an opener (with content such as dateline and/or salute) add it. For example: -->
<opener>
<lb/><space extent="3" unit="words"/><space extent="3" unit="chars"/><add place="inspace" rend="gray small" hand="#U">MS 004</add>
<lb/><dateline><space extent="1" unit="words"/><placeName><settlement type="city">Manchester</settlement></placeName>
<lb/><space extent="1" unit="words"/><space extent="3" unit="chars"/><date when="1858-01-28">28 <choice><abbr>Jan y</abbr><expan>January</expan></choice>1858</date></dateline> 
<lb/><salute>Sir</salute><!-- Change line info as appropriate -->
</opener>
<lb/><p>I have ordered
<lb/>about <measure>1600 <choice><abbr>lbs</abbr><expan>pounds</expan></choice></measure>
<lb/>of beads from 
<lb/><persName>Ms Kendal</persName> of
<lb/>5 Leadan Mall <choice><abbr>St</abbr><expan>Street</expan></choice>
<lb/>City - to be packed
<lb/>in cases of    
                
    <pb facs="liv_001193_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/>about <measure>400 <choice><abbr>lbs</abbr><expan>pounds</expan></choice></measure> 
<lb/>each. Each case
<lb/>to contain  a
<lb/>portion or <measure>1/4</measure> of
<lb/>each colour so
<lb/>that if we leave
<lb/>any we may
<lb/>always have a 
<lb/>selection to take
<lb/>on with us. The
<lb/>cases are to

    <pb facs="liv_001193_0003" n="0003"/>
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="words"/><space extent="3" unit="chars"/><add place="inspace" rend="gray small" hand="#U">MS 004</add>
<lb/>be marked ♁1 <!-- There is a symbol above the number that appears to be a "plus" sign. JM --><!-- See character added. AW -->
<lb/>♁2 <!-- The same symbol appears above this number. JM --> &amp;c <choice><sic><persName>D<hi rend="sup">r</hi>
<lb/>Livingstone</persName>s</sic><corr><persName>D<hi rend="sup">r</hi>
<lb/>Livingstone</persName>'s</corr></choice>
<lb/>expedition. I
<lb/>would like
<lb/>you to call at
<lb/>your <w>con-
<lb break="no"/>venience</w> and
<lb/>see if the cases
<lb/>are good. Take
<lb/>a note of them
    
    <pb facs="liv_001193_0004" n="0004"/>
<lb/>I have this day
<lb/>ordered <measure>5 bales</measure>
<lb/>of calicoes each of
<lb/><!-- There appears to be the number "4" in the left-hand margin here, but it is not clear if it relates to the text. JM --><add place="marginleft">4</add> containing portions
<lb/>of all the colours
<lb/>&amp; one all unbleached
<lb/>calico. Marked
<lb/>41 42 &amp;c to
<lb/>be sent as the
<lb/>beads must be
<lb/>to <persName>Mr Macgregor</persName>
<lb/><unclear cert="low">Laurds</unclear> stores at
 
    <pb facs="liv_001193_0005" n="0005"/>
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="words"/><space extent="3" unit="chars"/><add place="inspace" rend="gray small" hand="#U">MS 004</add>
<lb/><placeName><unclear cert="medium">Borken</unclear> head</placeName> for
<lb/>embarkation
<lb/>on the <date when="1858-02-15">15<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi></date>. Please
<lb/>take a note of
<lb/>them and an
<lb/>additional bale
<lb/>marked <unclear cert="medium">I</unclear>. A. T.</p>
<lb/><p><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>A packet of
<lb/><term type="foodstuff">preserved vegetables</term>
<lb/>was left at
<lb/><persName>Sir Morton Peto</persName>'s    
    
    <pb facs="liv_001193_0006" n="0006"/>
<lb/>for samples. 
<lb/>Captain <persName><unclear><choice><sic>Bedinfeld</sic><corr>Bedingfeld</corr></choice></unclear></persName>
<lb/>will order <del type="strikethrough">them</del>
<lb/>some from the
<lb/>same parties
<lb/>and you had
<lb/>better put yourself
<lb/>in communication
<lb/>with him and
<lb/>if he gives you
<lb/>the order to get
<lb/>them tell the    
    
    <pb facs="liv_001193_0007" n="0007"/>
<lb/>parties that
<lb/>the samples may
<lb/>be removed now
<lb/>your paintings
<lb/>are still at <persName>Sir
<lb/><choice><abbr>Mr</abbr><expan>Morton</expan></choice> Peto</persName>'s. The
<lb/>Duke of <placeName>Argyll</placeName>
<lb/>would like to
<lb/>see them if I had
<lb/>time to go with you.</p>
<lb/><p>Your pay begins
<lb/>on the <date when="1858-02-01">1<hi rend="sup">st</hi>February</date>
<lb/>so you had better    
    
    <pb facs="liv_001193_0008" n="0008"/>
<lb/>get ready for the
<lb/><date when="1858-02-15">15<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi></date> of that
<lb/>month. I shall
<lb/>be in <placeName><settlement type="city">London</settlement></placeName>
<lb/>on Saturday.</p>
<lb/><closer><space extent="1" unit="words"/><salute>and am &amp;c</salute>
<lb/><space extent="1" unit="chars"/><persName>David Livingstone</persName></closer>
<lb/>
<lb/>
<lb/>
<lb/><trailer><persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> <choice><abbr>T.</abbr><expan>Thomas</expan></choice> Baines</persName></trailer>
<!-- The name "Mr. T. Baines" appears in the bottom left-hand corner of this page. I am not sure how to encode this. JM --><!-- Fixed. AW -->


